body: "## Plan record\nDelivery plan for completing the schema-customization epic (pm-8jdc), executed 2026-06-03 on branch schema-customization-completion-20260603 via 2 specialized sub-agents, integrated and verified by the orchestrator.\n\nSteps (all shipped):\n1. pm schema remove-type [pm-k8ik — closed]\n2. pm schema add-status / remove-status [pm-e77a — closed]\n3. Per-type workflow allowed-transitions enforced on update [pm-f4r1 — closed]\n4. governance.create_default_type settable via pm config set [pm-jpwo — closed]\n5. Close satisfied stories pm-mt7k (schema list/show), pm-vhd9 (init --type-preset) [closed]\n\n## Why still open / exit criteria\nRetained as the epic's verification checklist. Before closing: re-verify each referenced child is closed with resolution evidence, confirm docs (SCHEMA.md/CONFIGURATION.md) cover all five capabilities, then materialize the outcome into a closing comment on pm-8jdc. The epic itself stays open as a living backlog."
